docs.abstract: China’s slowing economic growth and weakening consumer sentiment pose a challenge to an e-commerce giant with world-swallowing ambitions.
docs.snippet: China’s slowing economic growth and weakening consumer sentiment pose a challenge to an e-commerce giant with world-swallowing ambitions.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — After 24 hours of frenzied buying and selling, and weeks of advertising and promotions before it, the Alibaba Group announced that its sales hit another titanic high on Singles Day, the Nov. 11 shopping festival that the Chinese e-commerce behemoth cooked up a decade ago.

headline.main: Alibaba’s Singles Day Sales Top $30 Billion. The Party May Not Last.
headline.print_headline: A Big Singles Day for Alibaba, but the Party May Not Last

docs.abstract: Four Republican senators have expressed concern about President Trump’s potential pick for the Fed, making Mr. Cain’s nomination all but dead.
docs.snippet: Four Republican senators have expressed concern about President Trump’s potential pick for the Fed, making Mr. Cain’s nomination all but dead.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Herman Cain’s chances to win confirmation to the Federal Reserve plummeted on Thursday as at least four Republican senators indicated they would not back President Trump’s choice to fill a Fed seat.

headline.main: Herman Cain’s Fed Chances Dim Amid Republican Senate Opposition
headline.print_headline: Cain’s Chances For Fed Seat Fade in Senate

docs.abstract: A man spent millions on an enormous plot of land near Reno. Now he wants to build a community based on the blockchain technology introduced by Bitcoin.
docs.snippet: A man spent millions on an enormous plot of land near Reno. Now he wants to build a community based on the blockchain technology introduced by Bitcoin.
docs.lead_paragraph: STOREY COUNTY, Nev. — An enormous plot of land in the Nevada desert — bigger than nearby Reno — has been the subject of local intrigue since a company with no history, Blockchains L.L.C., bought it for $170 million in cash this year.

headline.main: A Cryptocurrency Millionaire Wants to Build a Utopia in Nevada

docs.abstract: The exiting German chancellor is celebrated as a rare source of European leadership. But many economists blame her for austerity that inflamed populism.
docs.snippet: The exiting German chancellor is celebrated as a rare source of European leadership. But many economists blame her for austerity that inflamed populism.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — In the political obituaries chronicling the  departure of Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, the world is preparing to lose a rare source of sober-minded leadership at a time rife with dangerous tumult.

headline.main: 2 Views of Angela Merkel’s Legacy: Stoic Leadership, and Economic Malpractice
headline.print_headline: Merkel’s Legacy, and the Fallout  Of Stoic, Hard-Line Leadership

docs.abstract: Last week’s protest could be a sign that highly-paid workers are losing patience with the technology industry’s worldview and embracing collective action.
docs.snippet: Last week’s protest could be a sign that highly-paid workers are losing patience with the technology industry’s worldview and embracing collective action.
docs.lead_paragraph: The most remarkable aspect of the walkout at Google last week may not have been that an estimated 20,000 people participated or that it had global reach, or even that it came together in less than a week. It was the way the organizers identified their action with a broader worker struggle, using language almost unheard-of among affluent tech employees.

headline.main: Google Workers Reject Silicon Valley Individualism in Walkout
headline.print_headline: ‘Workers Unite!’ Ethos Gains Foothold at Google in Bastion of Individualism

docs.abstract: An Oscar push is planned for “Amazing Grace,” which captures a transcendent performance by the Queen of Soul at a Baptist church in Los Angeles in 1972.
docs.snippet: An Oscar push is planned for “Amazing Grace,” which captures a transcendent performance by the Queen of Soul at a Baptist church in Los Angeles in 1972.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One of Hollywood’s holy grails, “Amazing Grace,” capturing what is considered to be Aretha Franklin’s most transcendent gospel performance, is headed to theaters 46 years after it was filmed.

headline.print_headline: After Years of Legal Limbo, Queen of Soul Sings Again
